title: Did Married At First Sight couples sleep together? | Daily Mail Online
text: Share 181 shares Later at the reception the couple kissed again, and then slept in the same bed in their hotel suite The next morning when asked the 'million dollar question' about what had happened last night, Cheryl said she wouldn't tell The following morning, the couple were seen together in bed both fully clothed. But when asked if they had slept together, Cheryl was coy. 'You'll never know,' she told a producer. But her new husband Jonathan cleared up the question, saying that he wasn't going to make a move. 'It was never my intent to make an advance,' he said. 'And the camera was there.' Cowboy Sean (right) and mining truck driver Susan (left) were the second couple to get married It was love at first sight for the couple, who seemed smitten with each other from the beginning Meanwhile the second couple to get married, cowboy Sean and mining truck driver Susan, enjoyed a smooch early on. It was love at first sight for the couple, who both appeared smitten with each other from the moment they met. They shared quite a few kisses during their wedding photos and reception, including during a sensual first dance. After the reception, Sean and Susan made the cameras leave as they had a bubble bath together in their hotel room The following morning Sean said the night had been 'sensational' as the couple cuddled up in bed Then back in their honeymoon suite of the hotel, the couple sent the camera crew away as they headed to have a bubble bath together. The next morning they appeared happy after a night together, with Susan revealing they didn't get to bed until 6am as they spent four hours in the bath talking. 'Last night was incredible,' Sean said. 'That bath was sensational.' The couple cuddled in bed and shared another kiss, with Susan remarking that she was 'looking forward to falling in love with Sean.' Scarlett and Michael (pictured) were married in the second episode of the show The couple shared several passionate kisses not long after meeting one another The third wedding of the show, between Michael and writer Scarlett, definitely had spark for more than one reason. Scarlett's mother Marie was unhappy with the groom, saying he was 'rude' and a 'pig'. Despite this, the couple were very physical with each other, kissing during their wedding photoshoot. They kissed so much that the photographer joked he had stopped taking photos, which the pair awkwardly laughed in response to. The couple seemed very comfortable with each other early on When they got to their hotel room, Scarlett changed into silky pajamas and the couple cuddled up After the reception was over, the pair headed to their hotel room where Michael carried Scarlett through the door. The bride then changed into a pair of silk pajamas and cuddled up close to her husband on the couch. They also appeared to be getting ready to sleep in the same bed, chatting to each other in the bedroom. The final pairing so far has been Nadia and Anthony (pictured) who were married on a boat in Sydney Harbour Nadia refused to kiss her new husband, which left Anthony feeling 'disappointed' The fourth couple to get married, Nadia and Anthony, were the least physical of the four. The flight attendant and racing broadcaster had a bumpy start, with Nadia refusing to kiss her new husband. Anthony said he was 'disappointed' and thought that his new wife wasn't as committed to the experiment as him. But later the two locked lips during a moment away from everyone else But when they got to their hotel room Nadia set down the rules, creating a barrier between them on the bed But the couple did lock lips later, after spending some alone time together. When it came to bedroom antics however, Nadia made sure that Anthony knew what the rules are. After negotiating that they would sleep in the same room, the bride created a barrier down the middle of the bed so there would be no touching. Married at First Sight returns on at 7:30pm Wednesday night on Channel Nine. Share or comment on this article 181
